  • Constructor Details

    • Path

      public Path(@Nonnull List<Tile> tiles, @Nonnull Tile startTile, @Nonnull Tile endTile)
      Instantiates a path for a player's pieces to take around the board.
      Parameters:
      tiles - The ordered list of tiles that pieces must progress through on the board.
      startTile - The tile that pieces should be moved from so that they can be moved on to the board.
      endTile - The tile that pieces should be moved to so that they can be moved off the board.

  • Method Details

    • getTiles

      @Nonnull public List<Tile> getTiles()
      Gets the ordered list of tiles that pieces must progress through on the board. This does not include the start and end tiles that exist off of the board.
      Returns:
      The ordered list of tiles that pieces must progress through on the board.

    • getStartTile

      @Nonnull public Tile getStartTile()
      Gets the tile that exists off the board, which represents where the player's piece should start from to get on to the board. This is mainly useful for building user interfaces.
      Returns:
      The start tile where pieces are moved from when they are introduced.

    • getEndTile

      @Nonnull public Tile getEndTile()
      Gets the tile that exists off the board, which represents where the player's piece should end on when it is taken off of the board. This is mainly useful for building user interfaces.
      Returns:
      The end tile where pieces move when they are scored.

    • length

      public int length()
      Gets the number of tiles in this path.
      Returns:
      The number of tiles in this path.

    • get

      @Nonnull public Tile get(int index)
      Retrieves the tile at the index index in this path. The index is treated as a 0-based index into the tiles of this path.
      Parameters:
      index - The index of the tile in this path.
      Returns:
      The tile at the given index in this path.

    • isEquivalent

      public boolean isEquivalent(@Nonnull Path other)
      Determines whether the path the tiles must take around the board is equivalent between this path and other. This ignores the name and intended player of the paths, and the start and end tiles.
      Parameters:
      other - The path to check for equivalency.
      Returns:
      Whether the path the tiles must take around the board is equivalent between this path and other.
